There's a photo of Michael Collins speaking at the podium of this event, in the Hogan-Wilson Collection of the <i>National Library of Ireland.</i> 

The Spring, 2010 (No 30) issue of NLI's &quot;News Discover <i>Lifelines</i>&quot; features this photo on page 8. It's captioned &quot;Michael Collins addressing a public meeting in Cork, March 1922.&quot;

This is likely <a href="http://catalogue.nli.ie/Record/vtls000279334" rel="nofollow">[View of Michael Collins speaking from podium, &quot;The Defiant Chief&quot;]</a>, in the NLI Catalogue, not yet digitized.

